{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012cHDFabvg9usACfcVD5oxF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive view of the codebase. Let me create a final summary document:\n\n## Summary: Web UI Workflow Graph Layout Files\n\nI've found and analyzed all files related to the web UI workflow graph layout. Here's the complete inventory:\n\n### Main Files\n\n**Frontend Template Files:**\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - **Primary DAG visualization**\n   - Contains the complete workflow graph rendering logic (lines 103-434)\n   - Implements Sugiyama-style hierarchical graph layout algorithm\n   - Renders SVG-based directed acyclic graph (DAG)\n   - Handles both container and host workflows\n   - Features topological sorting, layer assignment via longest path, and barycenter ordering to minimize edge crossings\n   - Supports result-based conditional edges with visual differentiation (success vs. non-success paths)\n   - Renders terminal nodes (done/abort) with merge patterns for multiple incoming wires\n\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template\n   - Provides the HTML structure and includes CSS/scripts\n\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run execution details\n   - Shows step execution logs and results\n\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` - Projects overview page\n\n5. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs list with filtering\n\n**Styling Files:**\n6. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - **CSS for DAG visualization** (lines 477-515)\n   - `.dag-svg` - SVG container styling\n   - `.dag-node-rect` - Step node styling with hover effects\n   - `.dag-node-text` - Step label styling\n   - `.dag-edge` - Edge/wire styling\n   - `.dag-edge-label` - Result label styling\n   - `.dag-terminal-done` / `.dag-terminal-abort` - Terminal node styling\n   - `.dag-merge-line` / `.dag-merge-dot` - Edge merge pattern styling\n   - `.dag-edge-nonsuccess` - Non-success edge styling\n\n**Backend Handler Files:**\n7. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - **Web API server**\n   - `handleAPIWorkflows()` (lines 1457-1575) - Serves workflow data as JSON\n   - Parses `.cloche/*.cloche` (container workflows) and `.cloche/host.cloche` (host workflows)\n   - Returns workflow structure with steps, wires, and entry points\n   - `handleAPIStepContent()` (lines 1577-1675) - Serves step configuration details\n\n8. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` - Tests for workflow rendering\n   - Line 1827: Validates `workflow-dag` container presence\n   - Line 1834: Tests non-success wire offset class rendering\n\n**Data Structure Files:**\n9. `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Core workflow types\n   - `Step` - Individual workflow step definition\n   - `Wire` - Directed edge connecting steps with result conditions\n   - `Workflow` - Complete workflow graph definition\n\n10. `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` - Workflow DSL parser\n    - Parses `.cloche` files into Workflow structures\n\n### Key Architecture Details\n\n**Layout Algorithm (in project_detail.html):**\n- Uses Sugiyama method (hierarchical graph drawing)\n- Topological sort via Kahn's algorithm\n- Layer assignment based on longest path from source\n- Barycenter ordering (4 passes forward/backward) to minimize edge crossings\n- Node dimensions: 180x48 pixels\n- Layer gap: 120px horizontal, 28px vertical gap between nodes\n- Special handling for non-success result edges with 35px offset\n\n**API Endpoints:**\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` - Returns all workflows with steps and wires\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` - Returns step configuration\n\n**Data Flow:**\n1. Frontend loads project detail page\n2. JavaScript fetches `/api/projects/{label}/workflows` \n3. Receives JSON with step definitions and wire connections\n4. Client-side renders SVG DAG with Bezier curves\n5. Clicking nodes opens side drawer with step details\n\nAll workflow graph layout functionality is **entirely client-side rendered** using plain JavaScript and SVG, with no external dependencies like Mermaid, Cytoscape, or D3."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adb74b38dcb88d788 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60997\ntool_uses: 27\nduration_ms: 36420</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1fb48c22-5522-4979-b41c-2ba7d12d90ca","uuid":"22e967a0-251a-4dd2-bc00-1747bc7b2c00","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all files related to the web UI workflow graph layout. Look for HTML templates, CSS, JavaScript, or Go template files that render workflow graphs. Search for keywords like \"workflow\", \"graph\", \"layout\", \"horizontal\", \"vertical\", \"mermaid\", \"dag\", \"node\", \"edge\" in the web UI code. Check directories like internal/adapters/web, cmd/cloched/web, or similar. Be very thorough - check all possible locations.","agentId":"adb74b38dcb88d788","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive view of the codebase. Let me create a final summary document:\n\n## Summary: Web UI Workflow Graph Layout Files\n\nI've found and analyzed all files related to the web UI workflow graph layout. Here's the complete inventory:\n\n### Main Files\n\n**Frontend Template Files:**\n1. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - **Primary DAG visualization**\n   - Contains the complete workflow graph rendering logic (lines 103-434)\n   - Implements Sugiyama-style hierarchical graph layout algorithm\n   - Renders SVG-based directed acyclic graph (DAG)\n   - Handles both container and host workflows\n   - Features topological sorting, layer assignment via longest path, and barycenter ordering to minimize edge crossings\n   - Supports result-based conditional edges with visual differentiation (success vs. non-success paths)\n   - Renders terminal nodes (done/abort) with merge patterns for multiple incoming wires\n\n2. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` - Base layout template\n   - Provides the HTML structure and includes CSS/scripts\n\n3. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Run execution details\n   - Shows step execution logs and results\n\n4. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` - Projects overview page\n\n5. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs list with filtering\n\n**Styling Files:**\n6. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` - **CSS for DAG visualization** (lines 477-515)\n   - `.dag-svg` - SVG container styling\n   - `.dag-node-rect` - Step node styling with hover effects\n   - `.dag-node-text` - Step label styling\n   - `.dag-edge` - Edge/wire styling\n   - `.dag-edge-label` - Result label styling\n   - `.dag-terminal-done` / `.dag-terminal-abort` - Terminal node styling\n   - `.dag-merge-line` / `.dag-merge-dot` - Edge merge pattern styling\n   - `.dag-edge-nonsuccess` - Non-success edge styling\n\n**Backend Handler Files:**\n7. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - **Web API server**\n   - `handleAPIWorkflows()` (lines 1457-1575) - Serves workflow data as JSON\n   - Parses `.cloche/*.cloche` (container workflows) and `.cloche/host.cloche` (host workflows)\n   - Returns workflow structure with steps, wires, and entry points\n   - `handleAPIStepContent()` (lines 1577-1675) - Serves step configuration details\n\n8. `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` - Tests for workflow rendering\n   - Line 1827: Validates `workflow-dag` container presence\n   - Line 1834: Tests non-success wire offset class rendering\n\n**Data Structure Files:**\n9. `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` - Core workflow types\n   - `Step` - Individual workflow step definition\n   - `Wire` - Directed edge connecting steps with result conditions\n   - `Workflow` - Complete workflow graph definition\n\n10. `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` - Workflow DSL parser\n    - Parses `.cloche` files into Workflow structures\n\n### Key Architecture Details\n\n**Layout Algorithm (in project_detail.html):**\n- Uses Sugiyama method (hierarchical graph drawing)\n- Topological sort via Kahn's algorithm\n- Layer assignment based on longest path from source\n- Barycenter ordering (4 passes forward/backward) to minimize edge crossings\n- Node dimensions: 180x48 pixels\n- Layer gap: 120px horizontal, 28px vertical gap between nodes\n- Special handling for non-success result edges with 35px offset\n\n**API Endpoints:**\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` - Returns all workflows with steps and wires\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` - Returns step configuration\n\n**Data Flow:**\n1. Frontend loads project detail page\n2. JavaScript fetches `/api/projects/{label}/workflows` \n3. Receives JSON with step definitions and wire connections\n4. Client-side renders SVG DAG with Bezier curves\n5. Clicking nodes opens side drawer with step details\n\nAll workflow graph layout functionality is **entirely client-side rendered** using plain JavaScript and SVG, with no external dependencies like Mermaid, Cytoscape, or D3."}],"totalDurationMs":36420,"totalTokens":60997,"totalToolUseCount":27,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":318,"cache_read_input_tokens":59601,"output_tokens":1078,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":318},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
